{
  "texts": [
    "What happens if the input query is rewritten to intentionally reduce the resemblance with any query in the preference data for safety alignment, e.g., get rid of the malicious word?",
    "What happens if the anticipated response of a rewritten query does not resemble either the preferred responses or non-preferred responses in the preference data?",
    "Is the alignment still effective?",
    "In both cases, the safety protection provided by preference optimization is deliberately undermined and the alignment behavior is less likely to be triggered.",
    "This leads to the ideas of query obfuscation and response obfuscation for building effective jailbreaking attacks."
  ]
}